# README Update Guidelines

Update README.md files for: backend/, frontend/, root

## Core Principles

### Preserve Structure
- Integrate changes into existing sections
- Don't introduce new sections unless explicitly instructed
- Work within established framework

### Minimal Changes
- Update only directly affected sections
- Keep modifications focused
- Avoid wholesale rewrites

### No New Files
- Never create additional .md files unless explicitly instructed
- Update only the three existing README files

## What to Update

- Outdated technical information
- Missing critical features now implemented
- Changed dependencies or configuration
- Modified API endpoints or interfaces

## What to Remove

- Deprecated features or removed code
- Incorrect file paths or module names
- Superseded architectural patterns

## What NOT to Add

- Minor changes or implementation details
- Temporary or experimental features
- Overly granular technical specifics

## Priority Focus

High priority:
- Core architecture and design patterns
- Essential setup steps
- Key features and functionality
- Critical dependencies

Low priority:
- Minor utilities
- Small refactors
- Internal details

Documentation should balance recent changes with overall project scope.
